comments.body:
Types should for the most part be nouns IMO. Seldom verbs in present participle like `Caching`. `CoinStruct` feels a bit WIP too.

Suggestions:
```suggestion
struct CoinState {
    const CAmount value;
    const CacheState cache;
```
```suggestion
struct CoinCache {
    enum State {
        CLEAN,
        DIRTY,
        FRESH,
        DIRTY_FRESH,
    };
    const CAmount value;
    const State state;
```

